Class ClassNamer

  • java.lang.Object
    • MinijavaBaseListener
      • ClassNamer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MinijavaListener, org.antlr.v4.runtime.tree.ParseTreeListener

    public class ClassNamer
extends MinijavaBaseListener
    A listener mechanism for creating and naming the klasses in the symbol table. When the ParseTreeWalker visits a node in the parse tree, it calls the enterRule method associated with that node. It then does the same thing to all children of that node. When the ParseTreeWalker exits a node, it calls the exitRule method associated with that node. This class is listening for the ParseTreeWalker to visit each node. When the ParseTreeWalker enters a class declaration, the enterClassDeclaration method is called. All children are visited in the same manner and then the exitClassDeclaration method is called. This results in an in-order traversal of the parse tree.
